    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "921915a4_6f3b4b2f",
        "filename": "include/effects/SkImageFilters.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 323,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-11T16:07:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have fairly strong opinions against SkCanvas\u0027 and others use of only a subset of an SkPaint\u0027s fields depending on the operation. In prior discussions, we were all interested in exploring APIs that split out the different areas/topics into specific fields.\n\nIn this case, that can be entirely represented as a single SkShader (using SkShaders::Color() if it\u0027s just a solid color). I\u0027m not worried about cons\u0027ing up a shader to represent a color in this case because the entire image filter pipeline is far heavier weight.\n\nTo me, having a temporary Shader() that takes the default FQ seems simpler than keeping Paint() around longer with these restrictions in play. Given the note, I should hope new callers do the right thing and make image shaders with explicit samplers and use the 2-arg version. I can update the name to temporary_Shader() or doNotUse_Shader(), deprecated_Shader(), or chromiumOnly_Shader() to better highlight this fact.\n\nIf chrome will be off FQ shortly, then I don\u0027t feel as strongly about letting Paint stay around for the same time frame.",
      "parentUuid": "385f184d_a81126f8",
